 detector efficiencies. Similarly, the standard\nsingle-node quantum repeater, scaling as $\\sqrt{\\eta_{total}}$, can be beaten\nwhen approaching perfect detectors and exceeding spin coherence times of 5s;\nbeating ideal twin-field QKD requires 1s. As for further experimental\nsimplifications, our treatment includes the notion of weak nonlinearities for\nthe light-matter states, a discussion on the possibility of using homodyne\ndetectors, and a comparison between sequential and parallel entanglement\ndistributions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Oct 2019 10:49:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 22 Oct 2019 15:37:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 3 Nov 2020 12:18:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-04"}
